    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>\n                  We have studied the correlations between twelve\n                  <jats:italic>environmental, economic</jats:italic>\n                  and\n                  <jats:italic>health</jats:italic>\n                  variables, by carrying out a statistical analysis of the fatality rate of COVID-19 in 14 countries. Our statistical analysis indicates that, among the 12 variables, the diabetes percentage of the total population and the extent of the population ages 65 and older in each country are correlated most strongly with the total number of deaths in them. Although the strength of the correlations between the variables and the total ND may change as the ongoing pandemic evolves, the study highlights the importance of integrating regional-specific variables in the modelling efforts aimed at projecting how the spread of the virus may influence different parts of the world.\n                </jats:p>",
